reviews.review_text: Looking for a place that is cozy, inviting and relax atmosphere? Well I just found one, this is the place where you can enjoy your pho meals. Very classy, clean and best of all the food is amazing! deliciously  prepared, service is uniquely delivered and graciously given..very budget friendly.. the staff are very helpful ,friendly and kind . Very highly recommended   service with care..

There are a lot of options for Vietnamese food on Victoria Drive, but La Maison Da Nang is my go to. I am a big fan of their vermicelli bowls, and the fried spring rolls are amazing. I love that they do the crispy thick wrapper, whereas many restaurants do thinner wrap. I ordered a grilled chicken with spring roll vermicelli bowl for take out, however there was some miscommunication as when I got home I realized they gave me pork. Regardless, it was so good that I ended up dining in the next day. This time I successfuly got the grilled chicken and it was also delicious. Ive tried their pho in the past and it is a good standard bowl of pho. The restaurant is clean, feels new, and our server was attentive and nice. Will be ordering from here whenever I crave Vietnamese!
Place is amazing! My first thought was how quality the food felt. Definitely recommend

The noodle, rice and meat were all really good. Price also very reasonable. Friendly and fast service. The only slight disappointment is the Danang Pancake - love the crispy dough of the pancake, but the filling would be better with a bit more variety and if they could provide more special soy sauce to go with the pancake. But it is still a must try dish.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much. Hopefully meet you again.

reviews.review_text: I came to La Maison Da Nang on the recommendation of a friend and Im really happy I tried this restaurant! We ordered the crepe/pancake (banh xeo da nang) , the shrimp-topped mini pancakes (banh khot), da nang udon (banh canh da nang), Vietnamese tapioca dumplings (banh bot loc la chuoi). My absolute favorites were the da nang udon (banh canh da nang) and tapioca dumplings (banh bot loc la chuoi). Those 2 items are definitely stand outs. The noodle broth was so tasty and umami and the noodles themselves were very delicious and wonderfully chewy but also tender. The tapioca dumplings were beautifully made and had a good amount of filling in them, the shrimp and meat inside were so yummy. I really like the food here and the zero pretentiousness. Definitely coming back and bringing my fam here.

Great food. One of the fewer locations for authentic Vietnamese. Love the amount of herbs and salad given to us. Had a special pho. It was ok. But the rest was really good. Could do with more top up on the tea but that s the only negative aspect. Didn t mark them down for that. Updated on the 7th July. Came back here again and the food didn t disappoint. Everything was great and authentic. Updated on the 20th Aug. came back again and still as great as ever. Portions are still just as large.

Lots of choices, good quality (tastes good and won t make you feel very thirsty after the meal like most Vietnamese restaurant did). Price is fair and portion is pretty large. Would definitely visit again! Food

A Vietnamese restaurant that is very modern, clean, organized & has a nice ambiance.  Food came out quickly and is excellent.  The soup for the pho isn t as flavorful as some other places but they will improve with time.  The three appetizers were fresh, crisp, & well presented.  Wait staff was polite, friendly & efficient.  Will be back again & recommend others to try especially if they like a clean comfortable atmosphere
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your comments. We hope to see you again at our restaurant to see our improvement day by day.

reviews.review_text: Great tasting food, reasonable price.  We will come back to eat here again!

This is our new favorite viet place.   Prices are extremely reasonable, portions are generous and food was tremendous!  An extra point for having a clean and modern dining space.  Staff were very friendly as well.  My only complaint, and this is a very small one was that my vermicelli dish had some water on the bottom from not being drained well after the noodles were boiled.  But this is very minor.  I would come back again and again.

reviews.review_text: La Maison Da Nang is now my favourite Vietnamese restaurant in Vancouver. The first impression was it s quite small but very new and clean. The menu got nice design and have many different choices. There are a variety of dishes from the centre of Vietnam. We ordered quite a few dishes today and they were all tasty and authentic. The price is very reasonable too. Would definitely come back to try others dishes.

reviews.review_text: Price: best in the city. Menu: lots of variety and options. Must Try: 25, 26, 27. This restaurant shows more inspiration of the Central Vietnamese cuisine. The 3 dishes listed are unique to the region. Design and ambience: modern and contemporary. Service: the owner is super nice but again, since this is a family business, they need more table service experience on that. :) in overall, Ill come support this new restaurant for real.

reviews.review_text: HIDDEN GEM on Victoria Drive! If you re looking for great prices and large portions, this restaurant is a must visit. The Vietnamese coffee and the crystal noodle in crab soup are hands down the best I ve had along the Victoria Drive strip. Recently, a few new places have opened in this intersection, but in terms of price, taste and portions, this small shop wins the battle.

reviews.review_text: La Maison Da Nang is one of my favorite Vietnamese restaurants in Vancouver. My brother recommended this place to me so I decided to give it a try. I haven t dined in before but usually ordered through DoorDash. As a Vietnamese, I could tell their food are authentic, very flavorful and delicious. Their food reminded me the taste of food and sceneries in the middle of Vietnam. I had Danang Udon and Fish Cake Vermicelli soup. Those were very yummy. I am excited to try all dishes from their menu soon. Their menu on the website got very nice design and has different selections . Price is reasonable given the big portions. Highly recommend!

one of my to go places for vietnamese foods in vancouver!!! the service is lovely and the food always hit a comfort spot for me! good portion, tastes very authentic. very blessed to have this place in the neighborhood

Great spot! We had the #27 (Banh Canh Da Nang) #30 (Bun Cha Ca Da Nang) and an order of spring rolls. Everything was fantastic. The Banh Canh dish was one of the better soups we have ever tried. Udon style noodles with a rich broth, shrimp and pork and great presentation. Really, really good. Fish cakes in the Bun Cha Ca were really good, tasted really fresh.  Spring rolls were amazing too. The best we have had since Thien Trang on Nanaimo closed down. Service was efficient and took all the steps for covid safety. We will be back to try some of the other dishes. Highly recommend.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for such lovely feedback! We hope to see you again soon. Best regards!

reviews.review_text: With so many Vietnamese restaurant on Victoria Drive I personally like LA Maison Da Nang the most. The food is good, the service is excellent and the place is always clean. I highly recommend them. My go to is the grilled chicken or pork with spring roll vermicelli bowl!
The Bahn xeo tasted amazing! Owner and server were helpful!

La Maison Da Nang on Victoria and E 36th Avenue is a delightful restaurant with bright, roomy and modern dining area and a spacious sidewalk/patio seating arrangement.  We had a very enjoyable lunch on the patio on this gorgeous sunny afternoon.  The food was fabulous and the service was prompt and pleasant.  The Shrimp Pancake, Deep Fried Spring Roll, Salad Roll and the House Special Pho were all absolutely outstanding.  There are numerous Vietnamese restaurants along Victoria between E 34th and E36th Avenue, which are all very good.  La Maison Da Nang is highly recommended.

reviews.review_text: Awesome Vietnamese food in Vancouver. The owner and her staff are super friendly and welcoming. I will bring my family back to try other dishes. Highly recommended!

I went here on Aug 18th (Tuesday) for Vietnamese food fix. I really wanted Bun Cha for my lunch and something else caught my eye off the menu. Never heard or tried  #37 Banh Hoi ($13.95) it was similar to Bun Cha from Hanoi. Long menu got my overwhelmed at first since I love BanhMi, Pho and Bun Cha and almost everything looked good. Waitress helped me answering my question on  BanhHoi and the Bun Cha(dipped noodle with meat and spring roll) on the menu. She was very informative and friendly. #37 is a popular dish from DaNang according to what she said. This dish was quite impressive it came with variety of leafy veggies and meats. Meats were fresh and tender. Im not sure if beef was in it, but skewered pork was tender and yummy. It also had chargrilled BBQ flavour. Shrimp with sugarcane was pretty good just that sugarcane was hard to eat. I nibbled a bite to squeeze the sugarcane juice. My dish was hearty and refreshing overall. Perfect summer dish I would say! It also felt like Vietnamese style of lettuce wrap with noodles and meat. I want to try different dishes next time; thank you, LMDN! I left the restaurant feeling full that day.

I went there with low expectations since my friend who went there when they first opened said I shouldnt bother trying and it doesnt look really busy compare to the other 2 Viet places at the same intersection. But Im on a hunt for banh canh (crab meat udon / rice noodles) so hell, Ill bite. And boy am I glad I did. Food: Ive tried the banh canh (obviously) and 2 of their appetizer dishes so far and theyre all delish, taste very close to what I had back in Vietnam so you know the authenticity is no joke. I must admit their customer service is not the best, waiters dont go around and annoy you with is everything okay every 2 minutes like other places, you have to make efforts to even grasp their attention. But I think this could be improved overtime or when it get busier. Tldr: excellent food, meh customer service but I see theyre reading the reviews and are trying so 2 extra stars for the effort. Also, they accept all kinds of cards, credits, debits, amex, you name it for payment which is a big plus since most of the places in the neighborhood are cash only or just debits.
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much for your coming and comments. Your comments are very important for us, especially for the customer services. Best Regards.

reviews.review_text: The reduced amount of MSG is wonderful! More restaurants in Vancouver should do this! I have uploaded a photo of the new menu with correct numbers.

I am in love with their pho and bun bo hue! The broths for both dishes are super flavourful and delicious! For bun bo hue, they have 2 versions: one with traditional pork hock and one with rare beef slices and beef balls. Im very glad they do this as Im not a fan of the pork hock but love bun bo hue. The beef stew and butter chicken wings are also really good! This is my new favourite Vietnamese restaurant now. Try the bun bo hue here. You wont be disappointed!

reviews.review_text: I had a lovely and delicious experience at La Maison! The staff are super friendly and are eager to help you out if youre struggling to decide what you want to eat. We ended up ordering the pho house special, 2 banh mi, and the banh xeo. The pho soup was tasty and the beef nice and soft, and the banh mi had tones of delicious lemongrass chicken and vegetables. The banh xeo was my favorite!! The yellow rice pancake part was wonderfully crispy, while the inside had lots of pork and shrimp. Then when its wrapped in lettuce and herbs and dipped in the sauce it becomes almost magical- the sour from the sauce, the sweet and almost spicy zap of the herbs, and of course the crunch and savoriness of the pancake itself- you just need to try it :) unfortunately we didnt take any photos because we were too hungry, but we will for next time!!
